    <section>
        <h2>Four Practical Tips to Avoid Aftertaste</h2>
        <h3>1. Stay Hydrated</h3>
        <p>A dry mouth amplifies aftertaste perception. Drinking water before, during, and after pouch use keeps saliva production high.</p>
        <h3>2. Place the Pouch Correctly</h3>
        <p>Position the pouch between your gum and upper lip, slightly off-centre. Avoid the back of your mouth where flavour compounds concentrate.</p>
        <h3>3. Match Your Nicotine Strength to Your Tolerance</h3>
        <p>Using too strong a pouch for your tolerance causes harsher, more noticeable aftertaste. Start with 3–6mg if new to pouches.</p>
        <h3>4. Refresh Between Uses</h3>
        <p>Remove your pouch after 30–45 minutes, rinse your mouth with water, and take a break.</p>
