        <h3>Why does my current pouch taste bitter after 30 minutes?</h3>
        <p>Several reasons: the brand may use low-grade nicotine salts; the formulation may be over-sweetened; you might be using too high a strength; or your mouth might be dry. Try switching brands, ensure you're hydrated, and consider a lower strength.</p>
        <h3>Does nicotine strength affect aftertaste?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Higher strength pouches (15mg+) naturally have more pronounced flavours and can be perceived as harsher. If you're sensitive, lower strengths (3–6mg) from premium brands will feel dramatically cleaner.</p>
